76561198035566667,Recommended,498660,24190050,"Posted: 8 July, 2016",all,Aegonn,"Mind Spheres is a cool concept and very decent for the price. It reminds me of one of my favorite physics puzzlers Enigmo. However I ran into some issues with the game during play that make it diffifult/cumbersome.For starters I am playing this on mac and starting around level 9 periodically the screen would go completely white and I couldn't see the puzzle anymore. You could click spacebar to initiate the sequence but then hitting R to reload would make the screen go white again. The only solution I found was to restart the game entirely.Secondly, the game the board each time you attempt the puzzle so you can't make small tweaks to execute the puzzle correct. You have to start from scratch each time.Last point - given there are multiple ways to solve the puzzle it would be fun to have a timer to show how fast you were able to solve the puzzle. Alternatively, achievements could be awarded for taking the most round-a-bout way.I really like this genre of games but I think it may require a couple of tweaks before recommending to a friend. Please keep making games like this though!---EDIT---After reviewing all of the updates that the developer has made, I would recommend this game to a frieend. I really like having the 'saved states' so that you do not need to recreate your work all the time and I have not experienced the white screen crashing as noted before. I still wouldn't mind seeing a timer and challenges eventually added but great work on the updates! Thanks."
