,Recommended,498660,31162199,Posted: 15 April,all,aeko,"I bought this game on sale last weekend for about 49 cents. I got the chance to try it out today and I must say it is a very nice game with about 50 puzzle levels or so. It begins as easy, in my opinion. You can learn very quickly the mechanics on the game which are simple and effective. For me the game is quite easy, only challenging part was the Eternal Loops (last part). The soundtrack for me is quite nice as well, very well done on the piano playing. I can't really find any negative aspect on the gameAll in all, I give this game 10/10 taking in consideration the following aspects:-Challenge-Price-Achievements-Steam trade cards-FunI recommend it to everyone who is trying to relax and play a nice little game for about an hour in order to complete it paying just the price of a beer."
,Recommended,498660,32377257,Posted: 12 June,all,CascadeHush,"A thumbs up, but only just.Relaxing puzzle game that is difficult enough to be interesting but easy enough to be completable.Each 10 levels is supposed to represent a different set or theme, but they just look the same. A simple colour change for some of the elements would have added some visual interest and provided more of a sense of progression.Some levels come down to very fine movement of elements, with a lot of trial and error, which is both fiddly and tedious. A tweak to the control scheme for the triangular rotating elements is needed, and a fast forward control (such as 2x speed) would be nice.But those small points aside, this a decent game. Put it on your wishlist and grab it when it goes on special for $1."
